And as a result of that article,

02:47:59.140 --> 02:48:03.140
they fired Lewis M. Steel.

02:48:03.140 --> 02:48:08.140
And I threatened

02:48:08.140 --> 02:48:10.140
and my whole staff felt resigned

02:48:10.140 --> 02:48:16.140
if they didn't reinstate him.

02:48:16.140 --> 02:48:22.140
Fortunately Roy Wilkins was in Paris

02:48:22.140 --> 02:48:29.140
and was unable to purchase stuff.

02:48:29.140 --> 02:48:32.140
So it all came out.

02:48:32.140 --> 02:48:37.140
And the I [Carter] was resigning.

02:48:37.140 --> 02:48:40.140
And I got a hero.

02:48:40.140 --> 02:48:45.140
Here I'm a black man with a pretty good job.

02:48:45.140 --> 02:48:48.140
I was resigning my job

02:48:48.140 --> 02:48:51.140
because they fired a part of it.

02:48:51.140 --> 02:48:57.140
The officers of the serial town.

02:48:57.140 --> 02:49:02.140
And so I,

02:49:02.140 --> 02:49:10.140
at that point, I was sort of tired.

02:49:10.140 --> 02:49:15.140
I didn't know where I was going

02:49:15.140 --> 02:49:18.140
with school segregation

02:49:18.140 --> 02:49:25.140
because I thought I had exhausted all the avenues.

02:49:25.140 --> 02:49:30.140
But when I threatened to resign

02:49:30.140 --> 02:49:37.140
if they didn't reinstate Lewis,

02:49:37.140 --> 02:49:42.140
I began to get revitalization

02:49:42.140 --> 02:49:47.140
because I thought for the wrong reason

02:49:47.140 --> 02:49:49.140
because here I'm black

02:49:49.140 --> 02:49:54.140
and I'm a resigning

02:49:54.140 --> 02:49:57.140
a pretty good job

02:49:57.140 --> 02:50:02.140
because a white man has been mistreated.

02:50:02.140 --> 02:50:04.140
So,

02:50:04.140 --> 02:50:11.140
I gave me a new lease on life.

02:50:11.140 --> 02:50:18.140
I print it probably

02:50:18.140 --> 02:50:27.140
helped me get a judgeship to I think.

02:50:27.140 --> 02:50:34.140
Because I don't know how I was first

02:50:34.140 --> 02:50:41.140
come up to be a judge

02:50:41.140 --> 02:50:49.140
when Thurgood Marshall

02:50:49.140 --> 02:50:54.140
and the Kennedy era,

02:50:54.140 --> 02:51:03.140
Thurgood Marshall was one of two judges.

02:51:03.140 --> 02:51:08.140
And they were ready to give him one

02:51:08.140 --> 02:51:11.140
but only at the district level.

02:51:11.140 --> 02:51:16.140
And he wanted something bigger than that.

02:51:16.140 --> 02:51:23.140
And the Kennedy didn't at that time

02:51:23.140 --> 02:51:26.140
feel that blacks were,

02:51:26.140 --> 02:51:28.140
this was too good job for black,

02:51:28.140 --> 02:51:33.140
a black man.

02:51:33.140 --> 02:51:40.140
So they came after me.

02:51:40.140 --> 02:51:48.140
And I had these people

02:51:48.140 --> 02:51:55.140
that were want to mitigate a judgeship.

02:51:55.140 --> 02:52:06.140
And Adam Adam Clayton Powell Jr Jr.

02:52:07.140 --> 02:52:11.140
And I had a sort of a conversation.

02:52:11.140 --> 02:52:17.140
And he indicated to me

02:52:17.140 --> 02:52:21.140
that I had to pay

02:52:21.140 --> 02:52:24.140
if I paid a certain amount of money

02:52:24.140 --> 02:52:26.140
for the judgeship I could get.

02:52:26.140 --> 02:52:31.140
So I told my advisors this.

02:52:31.140 --> 02:52:36.140
And all hell broke loose

02:52:36.140 --> 02:52:46.140
because they felt

02:52:46.140 --> 02:52:48.140
that was a big to do

02:52:48.140 --> 02:52:52.140
and so far so I ended up

02:52:52.140 --> 02:53:02.140
with the people

02:53:02.140 --> 02:53:05.140
have to back down

02:53:05.140 --> 02:53:12.140
because of the politics of the issue.

02:53:12.140 --> 02:53:17.140
And I always say that I was responsible

02:53:17.140 --> 02:53:20.140
for, from Thurgood Marshall to Thurgood Marshall,

02:53:20.140 --> 02:53:24.140
getting his corn of appeals appointment

02:53:24.140 --> 02:53:31.140
because all the hell

02:53:31.140 --> 02:53:39.140
about that was caused

02:53:39.140 --> 02:53:42.140
by my people

02:53:42.140 --> 02:53:49.140
that Powell had asked me

02:53:49.140 --> 02:53:50.140
for money for any kind of

02:53:50.140 --> 02:53:53.140
a dollar of money.

02:53:53.140 --> 02:53:56.140
And in the end,

02:53:56.140 --> 02:53:58.140
there was politics.

02:53:58.140 --> 02:54:05.140
He had the votes.

02:54:05.140 --> 02:54:09.140
So I was abandoned.

02:54:09.140 --> 02:54:15.140
And I ended up with Thurgood Marshall getting it.

02:54:15.140 --> 02:54:19.140
And I thought at that point

02:54:19.140 --> 02:54:26.140
that my chance of getting a judgeship

02:54:26.140 --> 02:54:29.140
had ended.

02:54:29.140 --> 02:54:32.140
Several years later,

02:54:32.140 --> 02:54:36.140
it kind of came to pass.

02:54:36.140 --> 02:54:38.140
Before I finish up,

02:54:38.140 --> 02:54:40.140
I just want to go back one more time

02:54:40.140 --> 02:54:42.140
on the school piece.

02:54:42.140 --> 02:54:45.140
Because when you left in 1968,

02:54:45.140 --> 02:54:48.140
when you left the NAACP,

02:54:48.140 --> 02:54:51.140
you were involved in the Ocean Hill-Brownsville case

02:54:51.140 --> 02:54:54.140
in the Intermediate School 201 case.

02:54:54.140 --> 02:54:58.140
And I think your fight for quality education

02:54:58.140 --> 02:55:01.140
for black children

02:55:01.140 --> 02:55:03.140
was beyond brown.

02:55:03.140 --> 02:55:06.140
And I think that you were involved in the North

02:55:06.140 --> 02:55:09.140
and deal with the problems

02:55:09.140 --> 02:55:12.140
with segregated and unequal schools in the North.

02:55:12.140 --> 02:55:15.140
So maybe if we want to reflect on that

02:55:15.140 --> 02:55:17.140
on the state of education today,

02:55:17.140 --> 02:55:18.140
what's happened,

02:55:18.140 --> 02:55:20.140
what hasn't happened.

02:55:20.140 --> 02:55:22.140
But your efforts in the North

02:55:22.140 --> 02:55:26.140
were really pioneering.

02:55:26.140 --> 02:55:29.140
In the North.

02:55:29.140 --> 02:55:35.140
The issue of segregation

02:55:35.140 --> 02:55:37.140
was not North South,

02:55:37.140 --> 02:55:41.140
it was Nationwide.

02:55:41.140 --> 02:55:46.140
The North and schools

02:55:46.140 --> 02:55:56.140
didn't want to keep the schools segregated.

02:55:56.140 --> 02:56:03.140
They were grueling,

02:56:03.140 --> 02:56:08.140
grueling, and some of those.

02:56:08.140 --> 02:56:23.140
But the North and school segregation

02:56:23.140 --> 02:56:30.140
was not the issue of segregation.

02:56:30.140 --> 02:56:38.140
It was the issue of keeping blocks

02:56:38.140 --> 02:56:41.140
and white separate.

02:56:41.140 --> 02:56:47.140
It was a national phenomenon.

02:56:47.140 --> 02:56:55.140
There has been no push

02:56:55.140 --> 02:57:01.140
recently to move.

02:57:01.140 --> 02:57:07.140
And I expect that at some point

02:57:07.140 --> 02:57:12.140
there was going to be an issue

02:57:12.140 --> 02:57:21.140
of this manly voluntary school segregation.

02:57:21.140 --> 02:57:24.140
I don't know.

02:57:24.140 --> 02:57:26.140
But right now,

02:57:26.140 --> 02:57:32.140
everybody is doing anything publicly.

02:57:32.140 --> 02:57:40.140
The issue is grueling.

02:57:40.140 --> 02:57:45.140
But I'm hoping at some point

02:57:45.140 --> 02:57:49.140
there's going to be a push

02:57:49.140 --> 02:57:54.140
for someone to

02:57:54.140 --> 02:57:56.140
and voluntary segregation

02:57:56.140 --> 02:58:02.140
to make it more a public issue again.

02:58:02.140 --> 02:58:07.140
But so far, nothing.

02:58:07.140 --> 02:58:09.140
I think the last question

02:58:09.140 --> 02:58:11.140
we'll do our filling in.

02:58:11.140 --> 02:58:14.140
In the light of your history

02:58:14.140 --> 02:58:17.140
and your long struggle

02:58:17.140 --> 02:58:20.140
in the civil rights movement,

02:58:20.140 --> 02:58:24.140
how do you see the significance of Obama's election

02:58:24.140 --> 02:58:26.140
related to your history

02:58:26.140 --> 02:58:30.140
and to the struggles you've been involved in?

02:58:30.140 --> 02:58:33.140
Well,

02:58:33.140 --> 02:58:36.140
there have been several things

02:58:36.140 --> 02:58:40.140
that happened with Obama

02:58:40.140 --> 02:58:46.140
that were unexpected.

02:58:46.140 --> 02:58:50.140
The passage of the

02:58:50.140 --> 02:58:53.140
one of the bills

02:58:53.140 --> 02:59:02.140
for equal education.

02:59:02.140 --> 02:59:08.140
One of the bills

02:59:08.140 --> 02:59:18.140
that Obama managed to get through

02:59:18.140 --> 02:59:29.140
came as a shock and surprise.

02:59:29.140 --> 02:59:32.140
But just the actual election of Obama.

02:59:32.140 --> 02:59:34.140
We were all here that night.

02:59:34.140 --> 02:59:36.140
Just his election.

02:59:36.140 --> 02:59:38.140
How did that make you feel

02:59:38.140 --> 02:59:40.140
in terms of your work

02:59:40.140 --> 02:59:42.140
to break down barriers

02:59:42.140 --> 02:59:45.140
to get voting rights in the South?

02:59:45.140 --> 02:59:48.140
Any thoughts on that?

02:59:48.140 --> 02:59:52.140
Just that moment?

02:59:52.140 --> 02:59:56.140
Well,

02:59:56.140 --> 03:00:03.140
I think that his election

03:00:03.140 --> 03:00:12.140
was certainly supportive

03:00:12.140 --> 03:00:19.140
of what I had hoped to achieve.

03:00:19.140 --> 03:00:25.140
But my story

03:00:25.140 --> 03:00:29.140
was not that I was not

03:00:29.140 --> 03:00:32.140
a black president.

03:00:32.140 --> 03:00:36.140
I wanted to still achieve

03:00:36.140 --> 03:00:40.140
equal educational opportunities.

03:00:40.140 --> 03:00:43.140
In fact,

03:00:43.140 --> 03:00:46.140
for all, for the poor,

03:00:46.140 --> 03:00:48.140
for blacks,

03:00:48.140 --> 03:00:51.140
and so that everybody had

03:00:51.140 --> 03:00:55.140
a chance of equal educational opportunities.

03:00:55.140 --> 03:00:58.140
Because I think

03:00:58.140 --> 03:01:01.140
that that's the key

03:01:01.140 --> 03:01:05.140
to finding black equality

03:01:05.140 --> 03:01:07.140
and diversity

03:01:07.140 --> 03:01:10.140
to, for me,

03:01:10.140 --> 03:01:13.140
Obama, is that everybody

03:01:13.140 --> 03:01:16.140
was able to secure

03:01:16.140 --> 03:01:18.140
equal education opportunities

03:01:18.140 --> 03:01:21.140
that it would be so.

03:01:21.140 --> 03:01:24.140
Now,

03:01:24.140 --> 03:01:26.140
that may be an elitist view.

03:01:26.140 --> 03:01:28.140
I don't know.

03:01:28.140 --> 03:01:34.140
But that's how I look upon it.

03:01:34.140 --> 03:01:40.140
And I am now

03:01:40.140 --> 03:01:44.140
too old to pursue it

03:01:44.140 --> 03:01:51.140
because I'm not one of those people

03:01:51.140 --> 03:01:54.140
who tried not to be

03:01:54.140 --> 03:01:59.140
who wants to stay on the stage

03:01:59.140 --> 03:02:05.140
long after I've been useful.

03:02:05.140 --> 03:02:10.140
I think that I've had my time

03:02:10.140 --> 03:02:13.140
and younger people

03:02:13.140 --> 03:02:17.140
ought to come after me.

03:02:17.140 --> 03:02:20.140
And there are a number

03:02:20.140 --> 03:02:24.140
of them who I think

03:02:24.140 --> 03:02:26.140
are going to take

03:02:26.140 --> 03:02:29.140
or take it over.

03:02:29.140 --> 03:02:32.140
So,

03:02:32.140 --> 03:02:36.140
I don't have any sense

03:02:36.140 --> 03:02:40.140
to find

03:02:40.140 --> 03:02:43.140
or to keep these for them

03:02:43.140 --> 03:02:46.140
to come out

03:02:46.140 --> 03:02:51.140
because

03:02:51.140 --> 03:02:56.140
I have,

03:02:56.140 --> 03:03:01.140
I'm sort of mentally

03:03:01.140 --> 03:03:04.140
fatigued

03:03:04.140 --> 03:03:08.140
and sometimes

03:03:08.140 --> 03:03:15.140
I have

03:03:15.140 --> 03:03:18.140
I do some little writing

03:03:18.140 --> 03:03:20.140
and stuff like that.

03:03:20.140 --> 03:03:22.140
But I really haven't done

03:03:22.140 --> 03:03:25.140
anything of any substance

03:03:25.140 --> 03:03:30.140
for a period of time.

03:03:30.140 --> 03:03:32.140
I'm going to get simulated

03:03:32.140 --> 03:03:33.140
to do something

03:03:33.140 --> 03:03:36.140
but I don't know.

03:03:36.140 --> 03:03:39.140
My feeling is maybe.

03:03:39.140 --> 03:03:42.140
I've done this since then.

03:03:42.140 --> 03:03:47.140
But I think

03:03:47.140 --> 03:03:53.140
I have

03:03:53.140 --> 03:03:55.140
I have a shape

03:03:55.140 --> 03:03:57.140
of vegetation

03:03:57.140 --> 03:03:59.140
and sometimes I

03:03:59.140 --> 03:04:04.140
get weary of it.

03:04:04.140 --> 03:04:09.140
But I

03:04:09.140 --> 03:04:11.140
I'm not

03:04:11.140 --> 03:04:14.140
wanting to go back.

03:04:14.140 --> 03:04:16.140
If I get simulated

03:04:16.140 --> 03:04:20.140
maybe I'll do some writing

03:04:20.140 --> 03:04:22.140
and stuff.

03:04:22.140 --> 03:04:25.140
But I don't know.

03:04:25.140 --> 03:04:26.140
Okay.

03:04:26.140 --> 03:04:28.140
Let's take a break and see

03:04:28.140 --> 03:04:31.140
what the floor has for us to fill in.

03:04:31.140 --> 03:04:35.140
So, can we start from here?

03:04:35.140 --> 03:04:37.140
All right.

03:04:37.140 --> 03:04:40.140
Speed, camera's rolling.

03:04:40.140 --> 03:04:42.140
Ready?

03:04:42.140 --> 03:04:44.140
Yes.

03:04:44.140 --> 03:04:46.140
My cord, George W. McLaurin.

03:04:46.140 --> 03:04:48.140
I think his name was George.

03:04:48.140 --> 03:04:50.140
George W. McLaurin.

03:04:50.140 --> 03:04:51.140
Start again.

03:04:51.140 --> 03:04:53.140
Start from the beginning.

03:04:53.140 --> 03:04:54.140
George.

03:04:54.140 --> 03:04:56.140
George W. McLaurin.

03:04:56.140 --> 03:04:59.140
I applied to the University of Oklahoma

03:04:59.140 --> 03:05:01.140
graduate school.

03:05:01.140 --> 03:05:09.140
And I was

03:05:09.140 --> 03:05:14.140
given what?

03:05:14.140 --> 03:05:17.140
Many of our

03:05:17.140 --> 03:05:20.140
the public felt

03:05:20.140 --> 03:05:23.140
that the public was the epitome

03:05:23.140 --> 03:05:26.140
of the separate

03:05:26.140 --> 03:05:29.140
because he was

03:05:29.140 --> 03:05:32.140
taught by the same faculty

03:05:32.140 --> 03:05:35.140
in the same class

03:05:35.140 --> 03:05:38.140
all he had was a separate

03:05:38.140 --> 03:05:41.140
seat in the lunch room

03:05:41.140 --> 03:05:43.140
and the classroom.

03:05:43.140 --> 03:05:47.140
And that was thought to be

03:05:47.140 --> 03:05:49.140
the first time a

03:05:49.140 --> 03:05:50.140
classroom.

03:05:50.140 --> 03:05:51.140
How successful it

03:05:51.140 --> 03:05:53.140
proved.

03:05:53.140 --> 03:05:55.140
Long.

03:05:55.140 --> 03:05:58.140
Great.

